<inglise> ANNEX </inglise>
<eesti> LISA </eesti>
<inglise> COMMON PRINCIPLES FOR EXPORT CREDIT INSURANCE </inglise>
<eesti> EKSPORDIKREDIIDIKINDLUSTUSE &Uuml;HISED P&Otilde;HIM&Otilde;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER I: CONSTITUENTS OF COVER </inglise>
<eesti> I PEAT&Uuml;KK: KINDLUSTUSKATTE KOOSTISOSAD </eesti>
<inglise> Section 1: General principles and definitions </inglise>
<eesti> 1. jagu: &Uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tted ja -m&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Scope of the common principles </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;histe p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kehtivusala </eesti>
<inglise> (a) The common principles laid down in this Annex shall apply to cover for supplier credit transactions with public or private buyers and to cover for buyer credit transactions with public or private borrowers. </inglise>
<eesti> a) K&auml;esolevas lisas s&auml;testatud &uuml;hiseid p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid kohaldatakse avalik-&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku ostjaga tarnijakrediidi tehingutele antava kindlustuskatte ning avalik-&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku laenuv&otilde;tjaga ostjakrediidi tehingutele antava kindlustuskatte suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) The common principles shall apply to cover for all risks as defined in point 4. </inglise>
<eesti> b) &Uuml;hiseid p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid kohaldatakse k&otilde;igi punktis 4 m&auml;&auml;ratletud riskide kindlustuskatte suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Nevertheless, the insurer may decide in each individual case to limit its cover to certain risks only. </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustusandja v&otilde;ib siiski igal &uuml;ksikjuhul eraldi otsustada, et kindlustuskatte andmine piirdub &uuml;ksnes teatavate riskidega. </eesti>
<inglise> (c) When all the obligations of a private debtor are wholly and unconditionally guaranteed by an entity which is considered public in accordance with point 5 of this Annex, the common principles for public debtors shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> c) Kui vastavalt k&auml;esoleva lisa punktile 5 avalik-&otilde;iguslikuna k&auml;sitatav &uuml;ksus tagab t&auml;ielikult ja tingimusteta k&otilde;ik era&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;lgniku kohustused, kohaldatakse avalik-&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;lgniku puhul kehtivaid &uuml;hiseid p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> When used in this Annex, the term'debtor' means either the buyer or borrower as referred to in point 1(a), or their guarantor with regard to the insured transaction. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas lisas t&auml;hendab "v&otilde;lgnik" punktis 1.a osutatud ostjat v&otilde;i laenuv&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i nende kindlustatud tehingu garanti. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Characteristics of supplier credit </inglise>
<eesti> Tarnijakrediidi kirjeldus </eesti>
<inglise> (a) The term'supplier credit' shall apply to a commercial contract providing for an export of goods and/or services originating in a Member State between one or more suppliers and one or more buyers, whereby the buyer(s) undertake to pay the supplier(s) on cash terms or on credit terms. </inglise>
<eesti> a) Tarnijakrediidiks nimetatakse &uuml;he v&otilde;i enama tarnija ning &uuml;he v&otilde;i enama ostja vahelist liikmesriikidest p&auml;rit kaupade ja/v&otilde;i teenuste eksporti k&auml;sitlevat &auml;rilepingut, millega ostja kohustub maksma tarnijale, kasutades selleks sularaha v&otilde;i krediiditehingut. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) Cover provisions for supplier credit shall apply where cover is given to enterprises established in a Member State in accordance with Article 58 of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> b) Tarnijakrediidi kindlustuskatet k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse juhul, kui kindlustuskate antakse liikmesriigis vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 58 asutatud ettev&otilde;tetele. </eesti>
